Method 3: XOR (O(n) time, O(1) space)

This avoids overflow for large n.

int[] arr = {1, 2, 4, 5};
int n = 5;

int xor1 = 0;
int xor2 = 0;

for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    xor1 ^= i;
}

for (int num : arr) {
    xor2 ^= num;
}

System.out.println(xor1 ^ xor2);
